lunaaaaa 01-Feb-21 03:27 PM
nice shaping, though I'd move "yet" up in the second bubble and downsize some of the fonts a bit so that the spaces outside the bubbles are more even. You always want to maintain a similar white space outside your text in each bubble so that it looks optically the same size to the eye (it maintains font size consistency). you can see how the space in "you want to come along?" is a lot wider than in the other ones because of how much less text it has in comparison to the other bubbles. To make it even, I would size down the other fonts a bit and sightly size up "want to come along" maybe by 1 pt
Darc-Star
also, is there a general rule on punctuation? never really paid attention to whether there were full stops and stuff usually, and i know i like to overuse commas should i just follow the script even if i think there should be a comma?
lunaaaaa 01-Feb-21 03:32 PM
for punctuation, if the TL doesn't insert it, the PR is trained to catch it. A full normal sentence in a bubble should always end in a period. A connected bubble... // should always have an ellipses at the first half of the sentence it fully connects to, and the second half of the sentence should start lowercase if it's not the I pronoun or something that should be capitalized. This is also the case with separate narration or bubbles that span over several places but completes on the next page or something. If the speech continues, put an ellipses. Though there are cases when you can substitute a comma instead of an ellipses as long as it's grammatically correct I was going to the store, // but then I changed my mind. ‚úÖ I was going, // to the store. ‚ùå (non grammatical placement, use an ellipses)
ellipses should always be swapped to standard ... three dot ellipses even though cn/kr/jp will use like .................. tildes ~ I always delete if they're not singing or drunk or something equal like that. I find a lot of tildes can be replaced with ! or . in English. We just don't use tildes that much. interrobangs should be ?! not !? ...! should always have their ellipses deleted, so ! or -! (if it's cut off) use the hyphen dash (-) instead of em dash (‚Äî) because some font glyphs don't support it or it'll look ugly sometimes (Spinnerracks ‚Äî glyph looks terrible...)
these are mostly pr things though

okk time for review
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812802773283241994/unknown.png
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812802838132555806/unknown.png
you ts'ed as "I think // you may have the wrong person" this is actually a QC choice, not a ts choice so I would stick to whatever the script has it as
on sfx - i didn't change a lot of the sfx, but be careful of font choices. you tend to use complete in him and akbar a lot. i usually use a different font for every different sfx and i also try not to use "speech" fonts like akbar, any of the BB/CC fonts used for speech (wild words, ccmeanwhile, mightmakesright etc.) and also to try to stick as close to what the sfx looks like in the raws
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812803027877494824/unknown.png
this one is more "squarish" it's a bit of a nitpick tho
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812815268824743936/unknown.png
for sfx, try not to space them apart so much? i know the japanese has it spaced out, but the way english vs. katakana/hiragana works is quite different. the eye reads english letters as a whole, not letter by letter whereas i believe katakana and hiragana is more letter by letter because its a syllabary system
also, i noticed a lot of rasterization and shaping layers? im not sure if you used a pen tool to write the sfx, but unless it's handwriting, always keep an editable text layer turned invisible + smart object it instead of rasterizing.
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812820269340688414/unknown.png
stuff like this shouldnt be rasterized
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812838640123641856/unknown.png
this is another instance of separation. it feels a bit unbalanced, but the japanese was on both sides of her head. i just moved the letters closer together and put it on the left side only
on narration - i noticed you tended to stack them up so it was more vertical - im guessing probably to help redrawing but english is a horizontal writing system and it's best to keep it horizontal rather than stacking it up like it's in a bubble. if it's not in a bubble, make the shape more horizontal for readability ease
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812804606185701396/unknown.png
this is one instance where it's too vertical and because of that, the shaping is off. if this were in a bubble it'd be fine, but it's floating narration, so you can make it horizontal (will suck for rd tho)
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812816080505798706/unknown.png
in general the narration placement doesn't help manga redraws tbh... cuz of how vertical the japanese is and how horizontal the english is
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812841985437990923/unknown.png
same thing here - if there's no bubble making you hyphenate, don't hyphenate. it breaks readability
or
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812842119097352242/unknown.png
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812842327852056616/unknown.png
be careful of your text placement. the period was clipped
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812845916608397332/unknown.png
i noticed the PR here was changed for shape
do not do that
sometimes the PR is not final because qc will make additional changes for clarity or grammar
so when you typeset, you have to work with the text you're given without editing to make it look better unless you're qc or the PR of that chapter
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812841640691367996/unknown.png
there was an extra space here which misaligned the centering. im guessing it was because it clipped into the sfx. you can just move the sfx a bit instead of adding spaces because it'll throw off the centering
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/784922083800252466/812851481816465428/unknown.png
crossbar/capital i here that wasnt in the script. try to copy and paste rather than typing it out because you can make typos or mistakes like this
ok thats it
good shaping/sizing for the bubbles!

Meiji CLRD Remember to grayscale images because these are physical raws. Image > Mode > Grayscale. Some of the pages are slanted as well because they were done on a scanner so remember to re-align and redraw the edges if the page is slanted. You can check by drawing a straight line on a separate layer or making guides via View > New Guide. Because these are physical raws, keep an eye out for artifacts like hair strands, big specks of dust, red lines running through the scans (scanning error), etc and correct them when you see it. As of now, the pages are slightly different sizes (ranging from ~1200w and ~2000h) because they're physical scans. we haven't decided on a specific dimension so don't resize them.
